+  local record, using Exploration 001 as the closure-burden input.
+
+## Findings Log
+
+### 1. Step 8 Needs A Finite Exact Closed Ledger, Not Another Screening Pass
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` The run-002 judgment explicitly says the local record does not
+  already support the existence of a small exact invariant ODE for
+  `F_SS(1/12)`.
+- `[VERIFIED]` The same judgment sharpens the branch accordingly:
+  exact closure is not bookkeeping around the real task; it **is** the real
+  task, and the branch may end immediately with a constructive non-isolability
+  memo if honest closure is not earned.
+- `[VERIFIED]` `decision-011.md` repeats the same controller instruction:
+  Step 8 must compute the exact forced-mode burden and decide whether that
+  burden yields one finite exact closed system or instead requires arbitrary
+  truncation or produces packet-growth failure.
+
+### 2. The Current Local Record Does Not Earn A Finite Closed Subsystem
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` Exploration 001 recovers one honest **classwise** closure
+  ledger, but not one finite exact support list.
+- `[VERIFIED]` The Step-2 interaction-template report says the exact data later
+  steps still need include:
+  one explicit wavevector family,
+  one exact helical coefficient ledger,
+  and one **finite packet-closure convention**.
+- `[VERIFIED]` The atlas-source intervention map independently says exact NS
+  automatically introduces extra same-scale,
+  cross-scale,
+  and mirror couplings once the desired circuit is active.
+- `[INFERRED]` Those two facts interact decisively:
+  the repository knows that extra companions are forced, but it does not know
+  one exact finite support set on which those forced companions stabilize.
+- `[INFERRED]` Therefore the branch does **not** currently earn any of the
+  positive Step-8 claims:
+  not one finite honest closed system,
+  not one explicit reduced ODE,
+  and not one exact interaction table that Chain Step 3 can inherit unchanged.
+
+### 3. The First Honest Obstruction Is Exact Non-Isolability By Missing Finite Closure Convention
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` Step 7 forbids post hoc companion insertion, alternate
+  bookkeeping currency, and witness repair.
+  Added modes are allowed only when the same frozen witness forces them on the
+  same ledger.
+- `[INFERRED]` But the current repository record does not say **which exact
+  companion modes** must be kept, because it never freezes the support-level
+  closure convention for `F_SS(1/12)`.
+- `[INFERRED]` To proceed from the current record to one finite closed system,
+  one would have to do at least one forbidden thing:
+  choose a new explicit wavevector/helicity realization after the fact,
+  choose which mixed mirror or shell-bridge companions to keep,
+  or truncate the exact packet at one finite support boundary not already
+  frozen by Step 7.
+- `[INFERRED]` That is best recorded as:
+  **exact non-isolability on the frozen ledger, equivalently an
+  arbitrary-truncation requirement before exact dynamics can even be posed.**
+
+### 4. Why I Am Not Claiming Stronger Failure Modes
+
+- `[INFERRED]` I am **not** claiming a proved class exit theorem.
+  The local record says class exit is a live possibility if closure requires
+  extra bridge structure, but it does not identify one concrete class-changing
+  forced mode for `F_SS(1/12)`.
+- `[INFERRED]` I am also **not** claiming a proved uncontrolled packet-growth
+  theorem.
+  The structural record makes packet growth plausible, but it does not yet
+  enumerate an infinite exact cascade of forced support modes on the frozen
+  witness ledger.
+- `[INFERRED]` The earliest constructive obstruction actually earned on the
+  current record is therefore weaker but sharper:
+  the witness is not finitely isolable on the same ledger without a new
+  closure convention or arbitrary truncation.
+
+### 5. No-Rescue Audit
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` No extra bridge,
+  shell-locked mode,
+  post hoc companion,
+  witness swap,
+  sign-sheet change,
+  phase change,
+  spectator-partition change,
+  or alternate bookkeeping currency was introduced in this exploration.
+- `[VERIFIED]` The same-currency rule and repaired Step-6 scorecard remain
+  unchanged.
+- `[VERIFIED]` The only additions recorded here are the closure-forced
+  interaction classes already supported by the Step-2 and atlas-source record:
+  mirror,
+  same-scale companion,
+  feedback,
+  and cross-scale back-reaction burden.
+- `[INFERRED]` Strongest claim now allowed:
+  the frozen Step-4 / Step-7 witness-local screening pass does **not** yet
+  lift to one finite exact closed subsystem on the same frozen ledger.
+- `[INFERRED]` Claims still not allowed:
+  exact dynamic pass or failure against `G_tmpl` / `G_leak`,
+  any class-level theorem about the full one-bridge family,
+  or any statement that `F_SS(1/12)` truly exhibits or disproves a near-circuit
+  under honest exact dynamics.
+
+## Dead Ends / Failed Attempts
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` The wrapper-launched explorer session did not land a report
+  sentinel during the bounded wait, even though its prompt landed in the
+  runtime log.
+- `[VERIFIED]` I looked for one already-frozen `F_SS(1/12)` support-level
+  closure convention in the inherited Step-2, Step-4, and Step-7 record and
+  did not find one.
+- `[INFERRED]` Without that support-level closure convention, there is no
+  honest way to write the Step-3 reduced dynamics without adding new
+  bookkeeping choices after the freeze.
+
+## Outcome
+
+- `[INFERRED]` **Class-retention verdict: not earned.**
+  The repository does not support one finite exact closed subsystem inside the
+  audited one-bridge class for the frozen witness.
+- `[INFERRED]` **Sharpest constructive Step-8 verdict:**
+  exact non-isolability on the frozen ledger,
+  equivalently an arbitrary-truncation requirement before any exact reduced
+  dynamics could be posed honestly.
+- `[INFERRED]` **Step-3 readiness verdict: no.**
+  Chain Step 3 is not well posed because there is no exact closed system for
+  it to inherit unchanged.

