+# Exploration 002 Report - Class Retention, Finiteness, And Step-3 Readiness
+
+## Goal
+
+Decide whether honest exact bookkeeping for `F_SS(1/12)` yields one finite
+exact closed subsystem inside the audited one-bridge class, or instead lands a
+sharper closure-stage obstruction such as class exit, arbitrary truncation,
+uncontrolled packet growth, or exact non-isolability.
+
+## Sources Used
+
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-008/GOAL.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-008/REASONING.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-007/RESULTS.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-007/explorations/exploration-001/REPORT.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-007/explorations/exploration-002/REPORT.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-004/RESULTS.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-002/RESULTS.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-002/explorations/exploration-002/REPORT.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/atlas-source/atlas-anatomy-exploration-002-REPORT.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-03.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-002/attacks/chain-03.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-002/attacks/chain-01.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/controller/decisions/decision-011.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/CHAIN.md`
+- `library/factual/exact-ns-tao-circuit-near-closure-screening/all-promoted-step-2-candidates-share-the-same-forced-exact-ns-extras-around-the-core.md`
+
+## Operational Note
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` The required local path
+  `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-008/explorations/exploration-001/REPORT.md`
+  is absent from the repository.
+- `[INFERRED]` I therefore reconstructed the Step-8 closure-stage verdict from
+  the landed Step-7 freeze, Step-4 dossier rules, Step-2 interaction-template
+  record, the atlas anatomy note, and the run-002 planning/controller packet.
+- `[INFERRED]` The missing sibling report is not itself the verdict, but it is
+  consistent with the larger problem on disk: the raw exact closure ledger for
+  `F_SS(1/12)` never lands as one finished finite support sheet.
+
+## Findings Log
+
+### 1. Step 8 must earn support-level closure, not repackage screening data
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` Step 7 freezes only the witness identity, packet semantics,
+  sign / phase / normalization sheet, fixed window, desired core, spectator
+  classes, and the already recorded static dossier coordinates; extra modes,
+  companions, and interaction terms are reserved for Step-2 closure
+  bookkeeping only
+  (`steps/step-007/RESULTS.md:140-152`).
+- `[VERIFIED]` The run-002 judgment says the local record does not already
+  support a small exact invariant ODE for `F_SS(1/12)`, and that exact closure
+  is the real task rather than routine bookkeeping
+  (`planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-03.md:56-73`).
+- `[INFERRED]` So the Step-4 / Step-7 witness pass is only a frozen
+  screening-level starting point. Step 8 still has to earn one exact finite
+  closure ledger before Step 3 can exist honestly.
+
+### 2. The inherited ledger is classwise, not one finite support closure
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` Step-4 `A_closure` requires only that all desired and
+  **classwise** spectator channels remain on ledger
+  (`steps/step-004/RESULTS.md:117-118`).
+- `[VERIFIED]` Step-2 results record the same forced extras at the class level:
+  mirror / conjugate companions,
+  same-scale companion triads,
+  long-leg feedback,
+  and cross-scale next-shell feedback
+  (`steps/step-002/RESULTS.md:72-76`).
+- `[VERIFIED]` The Step-2 interaction-template report sharpens that burden with
+  concrete examples of reciprocal same-scale updates, forced mirror triads, and
+  cross-scale back-reaction once `A_{n+1}` is present
+  (`steps/step-002/explorations/exploration-002/REPORT.md:161-186`).
+- `[VERIFIED]` The atlas anatomy note states the same structural fact in exact
+  NS language: once the desired transfer triads are active, extra same-scale,
+  conjugate, and cross-scale couplings come for free
+  (`atlas-source/atlas-anatomy-exploration-002-REPORT.md:17-31`).
+- `[INFERRED]` These sources tell us what kinds of extras are forced, but they
+  still do not identify one finite support list on which those extras close.
+
+### 3. The decisive local gap is the missing finite packet-closure convention
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` The Step-2 interaction-template report explicitly says later
+  steps still need:
+  one explicit wavevector family,
+  one exact coefficient ledger for all desired and forced triads,
+  and
+  one **finite packet-closure convention**
+  (`steps/step-002/explorations/exploration-002/REPORT.md:187-197`).
+- `[INFERRED]` That is the decisive Step-8 obstruction.
+  The repository already knows forced closure classes exist, but it still does
+  not freeze one exact finite support closure for `F_SS(1/12)`.
+- `[INFERRED]` Because the open item is the finite packet-closure convention
+  itself, the current record does not isolate exact state variables, does not
+  isolate one reduced ODE, and does not isolate one ODE-ready interaction table
+  for Chain Step 3 to inherit unchanged.
+
+### 4. Why the obstruction is non-isolability rather than a stronger theorem
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` The attack memo says the Step-4 witness ledger is not the same
+  thing as a finite-dimensional exact system closed under mandatory conjugates
+  and closure-forced companions, and that nothing in the Step-4 or Step-6
+  record proves dynamic isolation
+  (`planning-runs/run-002/attacks/chain-03.md:56-75`).
+- `[INFERRED]` I am **not** claiming a proved class-exit theorem, because the
+  current record does not name one concrete class-changing forced mode for
+  `F_SS(1/12)`.
+- `[INFERRED]` I am also **not** claiming a proved uncontrolled packet-growth
+  theorem, because the current record does not enumerate an infinite exact
+  support cascade on the frozen ledger.
+- `[INFERRED]` The first constructive obstruction actually earned is earlier:
+  exact non-isolability on the frozen ledger.
+  A finite closed subsystem cannot be named without choosing a new closure
+  convention or truncation rule that the branch has not already frozen.
+
+### 5. No-rescue audit
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` Discretionary repair is forbidden:
+  no extra bridge,
+  shell-locked mode,
+  post hoc companion,
+  witness swap,
+  threshold retuning,
+  alternate bookkeeping currency,
+  or post hoc rephasing
+  (`steps/step-007/explorations/exploration-002/REPORT.md:137-163`,
+  `CHAIN.md:82-84`).
+- `[VERIFIED]` Step 2 is allowed to add content only when exact closure itself
+  forces it on the same frozen ledger
+  (`steps/step-007/explorations/exploration-002/REPORT.md:148-154`).
+- `[INFERRED]` Therefore Step 8 cannot honestly rescue the missing finite
+  closure by stipulating one preferred truncation, one preferred companion
+  sublist, or one new wavevector/helicity realization after the fact.
+- `[INFERRED]` The strongest honest claim supported now is only:
+  `F_SS(1/12)` remains a frozen static-gate witness on the canonical ledger,
+  but exact support-level closure has not been isolated.
+- `[INFERRED]` The branch is still not allowed to claim:
+  finite class retention,
+  one exact reduced ODE,
+  or dynamic pass/fail against `G_tmpl` / `G_leak`.
+
+## Outcome
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` **Finite honest closed subsystem verdict: not earned.**
+- `[INFERRED]` **First decisive obstruction: exact non-isolability on the
+  frozen ledger.**
+  Concretely, the record still requires a finite packet-closure convention and
+  a full forced-triad coefficient ledger before any finite subsystem can even
+  be named
+  (`steps/step-002/explorations/exploration-002/REPORT.md:187-197`).
+- `[INFERRED]` This obstruction arrives before any stronger Step-8 verdict such
+  as class exit or uncontrolled packet growth. Those remain plausible, but the
+  branch already fails earlier at the isolation stage.
+- `[INFERRED]` **Class-retention verdict: not earned.**
+  The repository does not support one finite exact closed subsystem inside the
+  audited one-bridge class for `F_SS(1/12)`.
+- `[VERIFIED]` Chain Step 3 depends on Step 2 yielding a finite honest system
+  (`CHAIN.md:94-123`).
+- `[INFERRED]` **Step-3 readiness verdict: no.**
+  Chain Step 3 is not well posed because there is no exact closed system, no
+  exact state-variable list, and no exact interaction table for it to inherit
+  unchanged.
+
+## Dead Ends / Failed Attempts
+
+- The required sibling file
+  `steps/step-008/explorations/exploration-001/REPORT.md`
+  is missing, so there is no landed raw closure-ledger report to inherit
+  directly.
+- I looked for any local file that upgrades the witness from classwise forced
+  spectators to one finite support closure with one exact interaction sheet.
+  The cited Step-2, Step-4, Step-7, atlas, and planning records never provide
+  that upgrade.
+- I did **not** escalate to class exit or uncontrolled packet growth, because
+  the current record does not prove either one before the earlier
+  non-isolability obstruction already fires.

